  "text": "Second in importance were the peripheral TL-TR interactions (L2 and L9; Figure 4 ) previously identified as stability elements [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The reduced steepness of the folding transitions (Table S2 ; Figure S3 ) as well as a larger R g in 1 mM Mg 2+ indicate that a higher fraction of ribozymes containing L2 and L9 mutations forms nonnative structures that are more extended than native-like intermediates. Finally, the A-minor interaction between A97 in P6 and the P3 double helix contributed least to the stability of I C but had a comparable effect on the native state as TL-TR interactions. The perturbation (DDG N ) from the single mutations was consistent with $0.5-1 kcal/mol associated with individual tertiary interactions in other RNA molecules [CITATION_3] Fiore et al., 2009; [CITATION_4] , when the data were analyzed as in this study.",
